snippet.textDisplay: That voice is “still going strong”!! My mom was a huge fan for years and I attended a few concerts with her. In the 80’s a family member worked for Tower Records in LA, one day they closed the store for Neil Diamond to be able to shop in peace. When he tried to pay,  his Visa card was expired and Tower confiscated it. Somehow (uh hem) that expired VISA card made its way into our house and was treasured by my mom until her death. I have it now but unsure what to do with it, maybe he’d like it back!!!
